&lt;p data-start=&quot;515&quot; data-end=&quot;884&quot;&gt;At InHome Therapy, our Coordinator plays a huge role in helping patients receive care by connecting therapist availability with agency demand in real time. This is a hands-on operational and inside sales role where you’ll work directly with agency partners, internal clinical teams, and operations leadership to help drive visit growth and keep patient care moving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;886&quot; data-end=&quot;991&quot;&gt;If you’re highly organized, confident on the phone, and motivated by results, we’d love to talk with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;993&quot; data-end=&quot;1125&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU MUST BE IN TEXAS AND ABLE TO DO IN PERSON VISITS BUT THIS ROLE IS PRIMARILY REMOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;993&quot; data-end=&quot;1125&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU MUST HAVE EXPERIENCE WORKING IN THE HOME HEALTH FIELD (ANY ROLE IS GOOD JUST NEED TO HAVE SOME EXPERIENCE IN OUR FIELD)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary of Primary Function:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Coordinator is responsible for filling daily and weekly therapist capacity and driving visit volume growth within assigned IHT agency accounts, and will be hands-on in providing support to the back office team from intake to scheduling and throughout the plan of care. This is both an operational support and a tactical inside sales role focused on converting near-term opportunity into staffed visits through direct outreach to agency partners. The Coordinator exercises significant independent judgment in prioritizing outreach, determining approach, and making escalation decisions. This role operates with a high degree of autonomy within the IHT growth model and reports directly to the Operations Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact agency partners directly to fill open therapist capacity on a same-day and next-day basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, pursue, and convert near-term visit opportunities across assigned accounts through direct outreach and tactical selling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage service barriers and problem solve across internal back office teams to remove blockers to capacity fill and visit execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently assess account needs to determine outreach priorities that support business growth, adjusting approach as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track excess capacity identified versus filled and report net weekly visit growth to the Operations Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exercise independent judgment in determining when account risks, visit shrinkage, and service blockers require escalation to the Operations Manager or Regional VP of Operations versus resolution at the Account Manager level, responding with urgency and acting without requiring direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify account opportunities and at-risk trends and communicate recommendations to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Operations and Clinical to ensure internal execution supports agency commitments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain working knowledge of assigned agency operations, staffing cycles, and referral patterns sufficient to anticipate capacity needs and proactively position IHT&#39;s available therapist supply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional job-related duties as assigned,

